  "name": "Clinging Climber",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/items/inventory/rope.jpg",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<em>Using leverage and pure brawn, you can cling to a cliff face, ladder, or rope with your legs to free both of your hands to take other actions.</em><br/><br/><b>Prerequisites</b><br/>Str 13, Climb 3 ranks.<br/><br/><b>Benefits</b><br/>As a move action while climbing, you can cling to your climbing surface with your legs by succeeding at a Climb check with the same DC as that of climbing the surface as a move action. If successful, you can make attacks with a two-handed ranged weapon and reload ranged weapons until you resume climbing. The GM can rule that this feat doesn't work on certain climbing surfaces.",
